### Director of Evangelism - Dallas Campus

We are excited to announce our search for the Watermark Director of Evangelism. Evangelism is the heart and soul of what we are about as a church body and we are looking for someone who can bring leadership, direction, and strategy to our evangelism efforts across ministries and throughout our outreach initiatives. This key leadership role will help develop equipping, training content, and leadership of our Unashamed initiative, which trains and deploys our members across the city throughout the year. An ideal candidate includes a combination of strategic thinking, experience leading evangelism efforts and teams, apologetic background, and most importantly a white hot passion to see people equipped to winsomely engage others with the Gospel.

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=118){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/1hi6SZAW07oqIt03tvGqfd/c58d92adb724788ba9984cbc9ddf41a0/Director_of_Evangelism.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

### Administrative Assistant - All Campuses
If you are administratively gifted and would like to submit a general application for any future assistant positions, our team is always actively looking for people who have a passion for supporting staff teams and serving behind the scenes. Administrative Assistant candidates must possess a high level of hospitality, excellent organization, strong communication, and seasoned administrative skills. Two years of office administration is preferred.

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=21){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/20J3yHmHx1QwGeXr4mtk6t/7979e13a81efc7977e2202a2f1ee7d4c/Administrative_Assistant_Job_Description.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

### Watermark Resources Content Creator - Dallas Campus

We are excited to announce our search for the Watermark Resources Content Creator. Our desire as a ministry is to bring glory to God by equipping and inspiring churches around the world to be and make disciples. This role is responsible for the content creation of basic graphics, copy writing, video, and more to support social, web, and email. Ideal candidates will have a desire to apply their creativity, awareness of social trends, attention to detail, and ability to manage multiple projects at once in a way that serves the “Big C Church". Please submit your portfolio to resources@watermark.org.

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=110){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/487hzaiYOd6lqiIGSeqYG7/b5385330b0f241ec0f7b078f919bbb82/Watermark_Resources_Content_Creator.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

### Frontlines Director - Dallas Campus

The Connecting Team is hiring a new Frontlines Director! The Frontlines Ministry aims to serve and equip hundreds of volunteer leaders for the work of gospel motivated hospitality. This position is responsible for the vision and directional leadership of the Frontlines Ministry. This position provides an opportunity for someone who is team-focused, detail-oriented, and strategically gifted to excel.

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=117){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/33V298mvGptiFRRvxJ7ykn/dba6b0f596b67c74492088c9ede557c9/Frontlines_Director.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

### Watermark Resources Project Coordinator - Dallas Campus

Watermark Resources is looking to add our next Project Coordinator to the team. Our desire as a ministry is to bring glory to God by equipping and inspiring churches around the world to be and make disciples. This role will be responsible for supporting our mission by managing and executing a variety of projects, including – electronic asset development, production of video and audio resources, curriculum development, survey creation and analysis, and more. If you are looking for ways to utilize business and tech skills while also serving the “Big C Church", then this may be the role for you.

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=111){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/u2iDetr65EjQ0o2VQeRYZ/c8a1c868f3d1eb9493c5e7de6dcd50dc/Watermark_Resources_Project_Coordinator.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

### Newly Married Ministries Assistant - Dallas Campus

We’d invite you to consider joining the Newly Married Team as the newest Newly Married Ministries Assistant. This position has a unique opportunity to serve as a key player in the care of those married for three years or less looking to connect in community. The Newly Married Ministries Assistant is responsible for communication, planning and executing events, assisting in the formation of new groups, and general administrative team management. Someone who loves people, fun, organization, hospitality, and administration will thrive!

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=119){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/1blCMSRXqFNdT40lbEOOvm/bc45fab2e29970372c74b46b2ac5dafc/New_Married_Ministries_Assistant.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

### Students Care Coordinator - Dallas Campus

Watermark Students is looking to add our first ever Students Care Coordinator to the team, as we seek to be a group where every student is known and accepted, taught about Jesus, and challenged to grow. An ideal candidate will help accomplish that mission by overseeing all aspects of RE:GENERATION for Students, our 12 week, biblical recovery ministry for students in grades 6–12. Additionally, they will provide support for Watermark Students summer trips (Camp Barnabas, Dallas Experience, Mission of Hope), and coordinate the Watermark Students Podcast. If you want to have a front row seat to the transforming work of Christ in the lives of students, this role is a great opportunity!

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=128){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/3LmWnMt3QhYpyBCy2DUolV/b174568e37c9b9509367889e83076da1/Students_Care_Coordinator.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

### IT Project Manager - Dallas Campus

Do you love technology and the church? The IT Project Manager is responsible for leading project management initiatives and ensuring proper communication with key stakeholders on Watermark technology projects. This includes helping ministries solve problems leveraging technology and working with the IT Infrastructure and Rock database teams to provide solutions.

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=99){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/1jIwL8Ob2JNNSxENsZiClO/dcc20eea277dcf5f66bfac0634ddd7eb/IT_Project_Manager.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

### College Women's Coordinator - Dallas Campus

Do you have a deep passion for helping college girls come alive for Jesus? The College Team is looking for a woman who will set the tone and be an example to college girls across the board. The College Women's Coordinator co-leads all aspects of student leadership team and functions as the primary discipler of our female student volunteers. Additionally, she co-leads all aspects of female college community groups and is the primary discipler of adult volunteers. Lastly, as a ministry owner, she plays a vital role in weekly programming and ministry events. Is this you?

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=112){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/4s80b9TKUobDaHdXWqiuFe/0acaeabb2746030bf01762beff10d021/College_Women-s_Coordinator.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

### Watermark Resources Communications Coordinator - Dallas Campus

Do you enjoy coordinating projects, supporting creative disciplines, and providing clarity for others to execute their responsibilities? Watermark Resources is hiring a Communications Coordinator to manage and execute all marketing campaigns and communications initiatives for the team. This role will be responsible for supporting our team’s mission of serving the “Big C Church” by managing a variety of projects, including – master content calendar, delegation of work to team players or third party creative contractors, status updates and next step recommendations for communication/marketing workflows, and more. 

[apply](https://my.watermark.org/WatermarkForms/560?PositionId=108){: .btn .btn-primary} [full job description](//assets.ctfassets.net/hw5pse7y1ojx/7y6Xautccr137NJiFtH233/d606b373eeb7f3ee00a9398b39862d7a/Watermark_Resources_Communications_Coordinator.pdf){: .btn .btn-info}

